review_blob: A boring insipid beer. Could turn me into being a lager drinker! Manchester can do better than this.
Lovely looking when poured, nice head which did not disappear quickly. Rounded bitter flavor, perfect for drinking prior to supping some strong Belgian Ales, which is what I did.
Reminded me of a dryish Mackeson. A typical stout but a bit dry and sharp. Probably wont get this one again. May taste better in the warm sunshine though! No such luck at the moment.
Not one that I would rush to buy/drink again. Good color but to me a fairly salty taste. Not to my liking.
Average beer with a good color, light head bitter taste with a sweet finish. Enjoyed it but prefer most of the other Springhead range.
Very refreshing if served at the right temperature. Citrusy aroma, hazy white appearance. I dont normally like sour fruity beers but this one does it for me. A gem.
Very very pleasant. Full bodied bitter with a slight sweet finish. Head clears quite quickly and not much fizz, which is all the better for bitter.
Cant fault this one. Great flavour and could compete well with draft. Bit too easy to drink though so would end up puddled quite quickly.
Good quaffing ale for drinking at home whilst watching the 6 nations. Nothing special. Very light with an old fashioned bitter taste.

Large 750cl bottle shared with the loving wife. Actually if she loved me more she would have let me drink the lot :-) She enjoyed it too much so Ill have to get another couple of bottles and hide them. Great warming chocolate, toast, aroma. Rich and brooding,  black, hazy, and very frothy. Sweet and acceptably so.
2011 bottle, maybe should have left it a few more years to see what flavors were still to come. Lovely beer. Only downside is a bit too sweet so was a slow drinker.
beer_name: Gouden Carolus Cuvee Van De Keizer Blauw/Blue

review_blob: Cant big this one up at all. Out of a 500ML bottle bought at B&M; stores in Retford. Very fizzy when poured not what I expected. Nice colour but a bit sharp and salty on taste. Wont put myself out for this one any more.

First had this 40 years ago when I had my initial Trappist experience. After all these years it is the one and only beer that, in my opinion, has never changed. As refreshing, powerful, warming and moreish as ever.

beer_brewer_name: Brouwerij der Trappistenabdij De Achelse Kluis
review_blob: Even better than the 8 Blonde. Will def be getting this one again. Would love to taste it on draft.
Very pleasant but not exceptional.Aroma roasty, citrus, woody, Taste medium sweetness, Body medium body, sticky,.

beer_brewer_name: Brouwerij der Trappistenabdij De Achelse Kluis
review_blob: Very moreish. Couldnt believe the amount of initial head but that didnt stop me getting through it. Wife loved it equally.
Wonderful. Had a great 75cl bottle at new year 2013, sadly at home. Enjoyed it more than the champagne. Quality Trappist ale.

Drank this at the Bees Knees at the Springhead Brewery itself. This could be my lounge! Couldnt wait to taste it but spent a few seconds on the smell...caramel, chocolate, toast, earthy, vanilla. the  opened my eyes and had a look...black, clear, tan foam,. Then the first mouthful...medium sweetness, lightly bitter.... full body, creamy, soft carbonation, long finish, 

The best at the brewery...but my opinion!
